HEADWORD: Honiton lace
<hw>Hon"i*ton lace`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A kind of pillow lace,
remarkable for the beauty of its figures; -- so called because chiefly
made in <etsep>Honiton</etsep>, England.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Honk</ent>⟦br⟧
